<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Win7 Aero Theme with pushed taskbar button for active wi]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=4762&amp;p=27254#p27254"><![CDATA[
The same theme now for Windows 8.1 with Update 3 (November 2014). Extract to C:\Windows\Resources\Themes. And before applying, install UxStyle and make sure the Unsigned Themes service is running.<br /><br />It definitely makes a huge difference in <em>easily </em>spotting the active window:<br /><br />Note that this will only work with Windows 8.1 with all the updates applied and if you have installed a uxtheme patcher like UxStyle. It will not work with Windows 8.0 or 8.1 without Update 1 etc. <strong>Before you apply the theme, make sure UxStyle is installed and stop and restart the &quot;Unsigned Themes Service&quot; from Services.msc.</strong><br /><br />Everything else about the Windows 8.1 theme remains the same, only the look of the active window button on the taskbar is changed to fix the usability.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">Gaurav</a> — Mon Jun 20, 2016 8:57 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
